Here is the command-level audit of the "Bazzite Unified Home Server + Gaming Station Guide."

🚨 IDENTIFIED ISSUES & CLASSIFICATION

CRITICAL (Breaks system execution or locks user out)

SELinux blocks custom SSH port (Phase 3): Bazzite is based on Fedora Atomic, meaning SELinux is Enforcing. Changing the SSH port to 53222 in sshd_config and restarting the daemon without updating the SELinux port policy will cause sshd to fail to bind. Result: The user is locked out of the server permanently when they close their initial port 22 connection.

Fail2ban configured before installation (Phase 3 vs Phase 4): Phase 3 Step 4 creates a Fail2ban configuration and runs sudo systemctl enable --now fail2ban. However, Fail2ban is not installed until Phase 4 Step 3 via rpm-ostree. Result: Command fails, service not found.

semanage unavailable when needed: To fix the SSH SELinux issue, semanage port -a ... is required. However, the required package (policycoreutils-python-utils) is not installed until Phase 4. Fix: Base package installation must occur before any security hardening.

MAJOR (Causes service failure or security gaps)

restorecon executed before filesystem mount (Phase 5): The guide applies the SELinux context rule and runs sudo restorecon -Rv /srv/nextcloud-data before running sudo mount -a. Result: The context is applied to the empty directory on the OS drive. When the ext4 partition is mounted over it, the new root assumes the default unlabeled_t or file_t context. Nextcloud AIO containers will fail to start due to permission denied errors.

MINOR (Brittleness or inefficiency)

rpm-ostree override remove failure: If podman-docker is not present, the combined override/install command fails entirely, aborting the Docker installation.

Background SDDM config race condition: The 5-second sleep in the session scripts is a blind delay. If the system is under high I/O load and SDDM takes longer than 5 seconds to read the zz-session-launch.conf, the autologin will silently fail.

🛠️ CORRECTED & COMPACT GUIDE

Redundant explanations, "What You Get" tables, and non-essential architectural deep dives have been removed. This sequence is strictly ordered to prevent deadlocks and execution failures.

