Docker Status: docker info completes without sudo, confirming group permissions are active.

SELinux Ports: sudo semanage port -l | grep ssh confirms 53222 is listed alongside 22.

Filesystem Contexts: ls -Z /srv confirms nextcloud-data is labeled system_u:object_r:container_file_t:s0.

Fail2ban Status: sudo fail2ban-client status sshd confirms the jail is active and monitoring port 53222.

Privilege Escalation Protected: ls -la /usr/local/bin/start-kde.sh shows root root and -rwxr-xr-x. Any attempt to nano /usr/local/bin/start-kde.sh without sudo is denied.

📊 RATING SCORE: 4 / 10

Justification: The original guide is meticulously documented, features an elegant architectural design, and attempts to solve a highly complex, niche use-case (unified immutable gaming/server host). However, it scores a 4 because the execution order is fundamentally broken on Fedora Atomic. Applying Fail2ban before it's installed causes immediate script failure, and changing the SSH port to 53222 prior to updating SELinux labels locks the user out of their server permanently, violating the core requirement of safety and deterministic reproducibility. The corrected guide resolves these fatal sequence issues.
